# scope
# void = void-based AI-native terminal emulator.
# - upstream = ghostty-org/ghostty (zig + swift)
# - direction =
#   (1) grid mode   : native tiling/pane grid as first-class (not plugin)
#   (2) ai-native   : agent I/O, structured stream, tool-call protocol baked
#                     into terminal layer (not wrapper)
#   (3) perf-first  : speed / memory / GPU / syscall budgets tracked per PR

# active phase
- done   [P1] grid-mode toggle (cmd+G)
  shipped 2026-04-22 (commits 326e5f159 → 56dc8bea6 → 15ad6e416)
  what shipped
    - action.toggle_grid_mode + default keybind cmd+g (Zig)
    - Swift observer voidDidToggleGridMode in BaseTerminalController
    - SplitTree.grid(views:) — cols = ceil(√N), rows = ceil(N/cols),
      ratios equalized. Spec: 2→1×2, 4→2×2, 6→3×2, N=3/5/7 bias cols.
    - flatten-tabs-to-grid  : multi-tab window → single tab N-way grid
    - explode-into-tabs     : single tab with splits → one surface per tab
    - undo-registration suppressed during swap (cmd+g again reverses)
  design reality vs original plan
    - original .roadmap had "new renderer path for N×M tiling". Reality:
      existing SplitTree renderer already supports arbitrary nested splits,
      no renderer rewrite needed. grid() just builds a balanced tree.
    - cmd+G overtakes native Find Next — still need to rebind Find Next/Prev
      to cmd+opt+return / cmd+shift+opt+return (NOT done yet).
- active [P1.1] grid slot-spawn keybinds (cmd+ctrl+N)
  eta 2026-04-28
  why "N=1..9 키 눌러 grid 의 N번 slot 위치에 새 PTY 탭 스폰. 동일 slot 키
        반복 = 스택 쌓기. cmd+ctrl+0 = broadcast."
  blockers
    - first need spatial → slot mapping on SplitTree (leaves[0..N-1] in
      row-major order). should build on existing SplitTree.Spatial.
    - broadcast mode requires multiplexing input across all surfaces —
      intercept at Surface.keyCallback level, fan out to each surface.
- todo   [P1.2] find-next rebind + command-palette entry
  why "cmd+g is now grid toggle. native Find Next/Prev need new homes."
  plan
    - cmd+opt+return       → find_next
    - cmd+shift+opt+return → find_previous
    - ensure xcodeproj MainMenu.xib (or programmatic menu) reflects this
- todo   [P2] scrollback restore on abnormal termination
  why "Terminal.app restores windows + visible buffer on forced quit;
        Void currently restores tree/splits but not scrollback bytes.
        user request 2026-04-22."
  sketch
    - zig: surface_serialize_screen export → Screen.dumpString(.vt)
      capped at last N rows (2000?)
    - zig: surface_inject_screen export or init-with-replay param →
      feed VT bytes through Termio.processOutput BEFORE pty attach
    - swift: extend TerminalRestorableState with surfaceScrollback:
      [String: Data] keyed by surfaceView.id.uuidString
    - timing: inject during surface init, before first pty byte, to
      avoid overlap with shell's initial prompt
  open questions
    - alt-screen (tmux, vim) at save time — restore primary only?
    - cursor position after replay — end with \n to push cursor below
    - storage cap — NSCoder blob size budget per tab
- todo   [P3] stack-analysis
  eta 2026-05-05
  why "void renderer/apprt/terminal/font 내부 map — diff 최소화"
- todo   [P4] ai-native IO protocol
  why "structured agent I/O channel alongside PTY — tool-call / token-stream aware"
